---
<section class="bg-gray-800 py-16 px-8">
  <div class="container mx-auto text-center">
    <button id="seo-toggle" class="bg-transparent border border-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-700 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors duration-300">
      More About On-Site Climate Control â†“
    </button>
    <div id="seo-content" class="hidden mt-8 text-left max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Why On-Site Climate Control is a Game-Changer</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        Jobsite weather damage costs contractors over $2.5 billion annually. Unpredictable rain, humidity, and temperature spikes can ruin expensive materials like drywall, flooring, and adhesives, leading to costly project delays and rework. You can't afford to leave your materials exposed to the elements.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        Our mobile, climate-controlled trailers and containers solve this problem. We deliver a secure, perfectly-conditioned environment directly to your site, so your materials remain pristine and ready for installation. With features like real-time monitoring, robust insulation, and optional power sources, you get a plug-and-play solution that protects your investment and keeps your project on track.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.getElementById('seo-toggle').addEventListener('click', () => {
    const content = document.getElementById('seo-content');
    content.classList.toggle('hidden');
  });
</script> 